AGI - Journalist Franco Di Mare, known face of Rai, died. He was 68 years old and on 28 April he announced, while he was a guest at Fabio Fazio's 'What time he does', to be fond of an incurable mesothelioma and to have contracted him breathing asbestos particles in the years he was corresponding abroad.
"Abbraced by the love of his wife, daughter, sisters and brother and the affection of the dearest friends, journalist Franco Di Mare died in Rome. It will follow communication for the exequie" reads in a note from the family of the journalist who died yesterday.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Di Mare, on 28 April last, in video connection with Fazio, had shown himself with an automatic respirator that - he had explained - "allows me to be here" and his words had let it be understood that the situation was very serious: "I have a very bad tumor, linked to the presence of asbestos in the air. It takes because you breathe asbestos particles without knowing it, without realizing it, because a asbestos fiber is six thousand times smaller than a hair, six thousand times lighter than a hair. Once freed in the air it no longer settles on the ground, and has a very long conservation time, it can remain there waiting until 30 years, and when manifested it is usually too late". On that occasion Di Mare had added, with a thread of voice: "To say that with this end hopes is not true, because science always goes on."<br> And then, he had pointed his finger against the Rai leadership: "there are all executive groups, not the current one, but the previous one, the previous one again. I was asking Rai for the state of service that is my right, the places where I was, so I could try to ask category associations what to do, they all disappeared. If I can come to understand, and it is not that I have to do it by force, that there may be legal or trade union reasons, what I understand less is the absence on the human level. People I was talking to giving you - he had told you - because I was a Rai manager, they disappeared, they denied themselves on the phone, to me. Like I'm a policeman. I find only one adjective in front of such an attitude: repugnant". The next day, the current summits - the ad Roberto Sergio and the dg Giampaolo Rossi - had made known to have "come to know only last night of the dramatic story of Franco Di Mare" expressing "all his human closeness" and ensuring their "availability to do everything possible to allow the journalist to reconstruct what he requested". War outside and within us.
<h2> The cord of the Rai&nbsp;</h2>
"The disappearance of Franco Di Mare is for the Rai, for which he has always spent with passion and professionalism, reason of deep pain, to which he joins the gratitude for what he did during his long career that has often seen him in the front line to tell bravely the conflicts in the world. A passion that accompanied him also in the programs conducted subsequently, in the managerial roles covered and in the experience of the program of investigation 'Frontiere' he conducted until 2023. To his relatives goes the sincere condolence of President Marinella Soldi, on behalf of the Cda, the managing director Roberto Sergio, the general manager Gianpaolo Rossi and the company all". That's what you read in a Rai note.

