AGI - We need a pact for intergenerational equity in public policies. The young Italian business leaders gave rise to the first edition of Rome Summit>, an economic forum promoted by <a href="https://ucid.it/blog/2024/05/15/rome-summit-i-giovani-leader-dimpresa-italiani-incontrano-il-cardinal-parolin-e-le-instituzioni-15-maggio-2024/" The meeting wanted to start a dialogue between the Church, in the person of the Vatican Secretary of State, Cardinal Pietro Parolin> who opened the works, the Italian institutions represented by Vice-Premier Antonio Tajani and the President of the Chamber Lorenzo Fontana and the category organizations of the young Italian entrepreneurs most representative (Confindustria, Coldiretti, Confartigianato, Ance, ConfAgricoltura, Confapi, Federmanager and Confcoopera).
&nbsp;
"There is no good economy - said Benedetto Delle Site, the president of Ucid Giovani - without good entrepreneurs, that of the entrepreneur is a noble vocation: are words of the Holy Father. Giuseppe Toniolo, whose thought on the economy was fundamental to shape the Social Doctrine of the Church, rightly considered entrepreneurs the first cells of the economic organism. Prescinding, that is, from entrepreneurs and executives, it is not possible to build an economy really up to the human person. Someone might think of an economy that even entrepreneurs do without. Yet, Italy continues to be the home of authentic excellence, small and large entrepreneurs who the world admires for genius and inventiveness." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"But as today - he observed - is current how the economist Joseph Schumpeter supported: the entrepreneur is not simply a holder of capital (the so-called 'capitalist'), but he is first of all an innovator. If it is true that the entrepreneur is an innovator, this is double true for a young entrepreneur, who is now called to transform business models of the past and imagine new ones". Istat's data on the collapse of births in Italy, which is likely to compromise in the coming years the system of welfare, consumption and investments. The data of Infocamere and Cerved on the decline of entrepreneurship under 35, at the detriment of the levels of employment, innovation and competitiveness of our economy, are the result, as well as of a cultural climate unfavorable to the new life and youth also of the irrelevantness of the new generations in the weighting of public policies.
&nbsp;
The cut of tax pressure, in this regard, risks losing effectiveness: to be distributed indistinctly to the widest possible audience of beneficiaries without taking into consideration the asymmetric impact that before pandemic and then the energy crisis have had on young people, unfavoring them in every area: "Denatality and escape of brains abroad, where it is often easier to do business, are - said Delle Site - our Achilles heel. Italy continues to be an unfavourable ecosystem for a young man who, risking, tries to embark on a seizure of fixed costs, fiscal and contributory pressure, bureaucracy, a real brake on youth entrepreneurship, vice versa the assumption of motherhood and paternity is postponed over time also for the absence of a real welfare dedicated to the protection of new life and young life. No one seems to realize that the absence of an important investment line on the new generations is no longer sustainable and will end up being contrary to the common good, to the good of all".
&nbsp;
It is therefore a pact for intergenerational equity in public policies, supporting the new forms of welfare put in place in an innovative way by many companies, and going specifically to increase for families and entrepreneurs under 35 the various benefits, whether they are bonuses or tax deductions and tax credits. This in the perspective of ensuring that all young people are free to assume paternity and maternity in respect of their fertile age, even in view of the fact that a family that opens up early in life has greater chances of going beyond the first child. So to support entrepreneurship and youth employment. This intervention on the tax is feasible at zero cost, without causing additional charges for the State, with a slight reduction in the intensity of bonuses and deductions from the current general taxation >: "It is therefore necessary - it has emphasized Delle Site - to remodel the policies for sustainability, in Italy and in the rest of the Western world, so that they are guided by an integral ecology, that in itself also recomprehensive an ecology of the human. Today it is necessary that Italy become the leader of a new model of sustainable development. Our companies can play a key role, provided sustainability is declined in the perspective of integral ecology: This is why we ask the public to recognize the social role of the enterprises and the wider valorization, starting from the rules governing our budgets, of the so-called intangible assets: creating employment, training, investing in human capital, developing new innovative forms of welfare, incubating start-ups, our companies play a role not only private but also public". &nbsp;

